==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: peewit
<hw>peewit</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A large crested Old World plover
having wattles and spurs; the pewit.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lapwing, green plover, pewit, peevit,
peerwit.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any of several small olive-colored woodland
flycatchers of eastern North America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pewee, peewee, pewit, wood pewee, <spn>Contopus
virens</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peg</ent>⟦br⟧
